  "prompt": "Which phone is best to buy under 17000 rs?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, here are some of the best smartphones under **\u20b917,000** in India, offering great value for money in terms of performance, camera, battery life, and features. Prices may vary depending on offers and availability.\n\n---\n\n### **1. Realme Narzo 60x 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.72\" FHD+ 120Hz Display\n     - MediaTek Dimensity 6100+ 5G Processor\n     - 50MP Dual Camera\n     - 5000mAh Battery with 33W Fast Charging\n   - **Why Buy?** Solid performance, 5G support, and a smooth display.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Redmi 12 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.79\" FHD+ 90Hz Display\n     - Snapdragon 4 Gen 2 5G Processor\n     - 50MP Dual Camera\n     - 5000mAh Battery with 18W Charging\n   - **Why Buy?** Great performance, large display, and 5G connectivity.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Samsung Galaxy M14 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.6\" FHD+ 90Hz Display\n     - Exynos 1330 5G Processor\n     - 50MP Triple Camera\n     - 6000mAh Battery with 25W Charging\n   - **Why Buy?** Massive battery, Samsung's reliable software, and 5G support.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Infinix Zero 30 4G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.78\" FHD+ 144Hz AMOLED Display\n     - MediaTek Helio G99 Processor\n     - 108MP Triple Camera\n     - 5000mAh Battery with 68W Fast Charging\n   - **Why Buy?** Stunning AMOLED display, fast charging, and a high-resolution camera.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Poco M6 Pro 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.79\" FHD+ 90Hz Display\n     - MediaTek Dimensity 6100+ 5G Processor\n     - 50MP Dual Camera\n     - 5000mAh Battery with 18W Charging\n   - **Why Buy?** Reliable performance and 5G support at an affordable price.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Motorola G54 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.5\" FHD+ 120Hz Display\n     - MediaTek Dimensity 7020 5G Processor\n     - 50MP Dual Camera\n     - 5000mAh Battery with 15W Charging\n   - **Why Buy?** Clean Android experience, good display, and 5G support.\n\n---\n\n### **Things to Consider Before Buying:**\n- **Performance:** Look for a processor that suits your usage (MediaTek Dimensity or Snapdragon series are good).\n- **Display:** Higher refresh rate (90Hz/120Hz) for smoother scrolling.\n- **Battery:** 5000mAh or more for all-day usage.\n- **Camera:** 50MP or higher for better photo quality.\n- **Software:** Clean UI (like Motorola) or feature-rich UI (like Realme/Poco).\n\n---\n\n**Best Value Pick:** Redmi 12 5G for its overall performance and 5G support at an affordable price.  \n**Premium Pick:** Infinix Zero 30 4G for its AMOLED display and fast charging.  \n\nMake sure to check for ongoing deals on platforms like **Amazon, Flipkart, or official brand stores** for additional discounts.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
